dcterms:description: The ImageCLEF 2016 Compound Figure Separation Database is a dataset used for evaluating compound figure separation methods, containing various types of organs and resources of large-scale medical images.

dcterms:description: Glomeruli-2000 is an in-house dataset consisting of 917 training and 917 testing real figure plots from the American Journal of Kidney Diseases, annotated with four classes of glomeruli.
dcterms:title: Glomeruli-2000

dcterms:description: NIH Open-i is a multimodal biomedical information retrieval system that provides access to a large collection of biomedical images.
dcterms:title: NIH Open-i

dcterms:description: The web-mined glomerular dataset consists of images collected from online resources, specifically targeting glomeruli pathology images.
dcterms:title: Web-mined glomerular dataset

dcterms:description: The ImageCLEF Medical dataset is a widely used testbed for compound image separation tasks, containing a variety of annotated multi-panel figures.
dcterms:title: ImageCLEF Medical dataset
